messages.content: “...So...what do I do?” Wander asked, holding a long red scarf.
Sarcio was trainin and gainin
Polaris didn't realize where he was going until he got there, looking around at the training area with an internal sigh.
He hadn't been there since he began his first mission..
Sarcio was on the treadmill
He had music blASTING in his ears
Malachite trails after him, clinging onto his arm.
"..." he stared at Sarcio for a moment in disbelief at the volume of his music, before looking down at Malachite. "Wanna spar?"

Malachite blinks. They haven't sparred in... god, he doesn't know how long it's been.
"... I'd like that."
Polaris hummed, turning to walk to the sparring rooms.
He chose the largest one, not entirely enjoying the small size of the other rooms. This one felt more... open. He felt like Malachite would also appreciate the ranged space.

Malachite releases Polaris' arm and starts taking a few layers off. He tosses his oversized sweater into a corner and tightens the borrowed belt.
"Ready?"
Polaris removes his own shirt, forgetting he had nothing underneath but being a bit too out of touch to care. "Mm."
Sarcio's ear buds said "You got the touch. You got the powerrrrrrrrrrrrrrrrrrrr"

Malachite stretches his shoulders out, then takes a deep breath, summoning Hierophant. His stand ripples out of him as he exhales, and the silvery tendrils shimmer into existence and start slowly undulating, waiting for Polaris to make the first move.

*He's letting me strike first? How kind...* he sarcastically thinks to himself. Nobody realizes this, but personally, he's more of an offense type than a defense type. Starting fights isn't his thing. He runs towards Malachite anyways.
Summoning Star Platinum, he combines their footing to launch him into the air, bringing his fists together to slam down on Malachite.
Malachite weaves out of the way, tentacles lashing out to grab Star Platinum's fist.
He dashes behind Polaris; his tentacles draw back, then whip forward and try to catch Polaris' ankles.
He lets the tentacle wrap around his ankle, grabbing the appendage and yanking it harshly, summoning Star to his side again to make his grip stronger.
Malachite yelps and flinches away, then regains his footing and attacks again, going for the knees this time.
Sarcio got off the treadmill, pausing his 80's workout music playlist, then he sees something familiar

*Shit—* he thinks hurriedly. He hadn't been able to regain his footing again, and the tentacles wrapped around his knees. He attempted to have Star rip them apart, but he tripped, using his arms to can ch himself.
"Star Platinum?"
He takes the opportunity to wrap Polaris in the tendrils, forcing his arms against his sides.

"*God,*" he muttered, struggling against the tendrils. He didn't have his footing, but he did have one thing—
"Star Platinum, ときょとまれ."
Time stopped.

Polaris had Star Platinum rip the tendrils off of his body.
*1.*
He managed to stand up, shaking away his dizziness and aiming his eyes on Malachite again.
*2, 3.*

Running over to Malachite, he quickly shoved the other to the ground, holding the smaller's arms behind his back.
*4, 5.*
"*Time resumes.*"

Malachite gasps and struggles for a moment as he finds himself pinned, then calms down. A shit-eating grin spreads across his face. *If he wants to fight dirty...
"Hahh..., this is kinda like a reversal of last night, huh, Polaris?"
"Wh—" Polaris's eyes widen, his face bright violet, and he lets go of Malachite, stumbling back a few steps. "Y-you..!?"
Sarcio was invested in the fight before Mala made...that remark.
He tried to forget that for a moment. "Mister Kujo!"
Polaris turned his head, coughing into his hand and trying (*& completely failing*) to tone down his blush.
*Never figured out his mun name...* Sarcio decided to show Crazy Diamond to see if Polaris remembered him
Malachite strikes while the iron is hot. His tentacles snake around Polaris and dive into his mouth, writhing around and wiggling their way into his brain. *Gotcha, bitch*

*OH THIS MOTHER FUCKER—* Polaris's eyes widened in surprise. He JUST spotted the other mun, and the dude was bound to be freaked out by this. He used Star Platinum to get a strong grip on Malachite, using one of his hands to point at the other mun he noticed.
Sarcio awkwardly waved. "is this an enemy stand attack or?"

Malachite freezes, tendrils still wrapping around Polaris' brain. *Oh. Huh.*
He'll worry about this asshole later. He's got a fight to win. He continues focusing his energy into fuzzing out Polaris' brainwaves.
*THIS LITTLE-* Polaris thought to himself. *MALACHITE GET OUT OF MY FUCKING HEAD THAT'S MY TEEN UNCLE!* he yelled, hoping Hierophant could hear him.

Malachite can't find it within himself to care.
"Give up. Say I win."
*Never.*

*"Give. Up."*
He tightens his hold on his boyfriend's brain, cutting off a good part of it. He doesn't plan on taking over completely unless Polaris keeps resisting.
*I— Malachite my kid uncle is RIGHT THERE I don't want to traumatize him right now!?*
Sarcio was confused. That stand he saw gave him a similar vibe to a story he had heard from his dad.

Malachite transmits his thoughts directly into his brain.
*"Oh please. It's not like you haven't already done that. Have you seen your neck recently?"*
*MALACHITE—* he thought particularly loudly. *NOW IS NOT THE TIME TO GIVE MY TEEN UNCLE THIS KIND OF FIRST IMPRESSION!!*
"What was the guy's name ...uh....Av...doll? Nah, that can't be right...."
He pointed to Malachite. "hey, your muse is uh....Hol Horse, right?"
((*pfft*

*"Shithead."*
He hisses, voice rattling around in Polaris' head.
*"You took your sweater off. You realize the implications of the bruises on your neck, right? They sure as hell don't look like injuries."*
*MALACHITE WHEN YOU LET GO OF MY BRAIN I AM GOING TO STRANGLE YOU LIKE A GOD DAMN BALLOON ANIMAL*
*"Fucking **submit** and this can all be over. Your other option is that I finish the job and possess you. Do you want that?"*

Getting to the training room, he went to the same room as last time. He's been feeling especially claustrophobic since he was locked in practically a damn jail cell.

"You wanna start?"
Malachite shrugs off his shirt and removes his glasses, setting both items off to the side.

He pulls his shirt off, too, glad he managed to get on some comfortable sweatpants before all this shit happened.
"Hm," he hummed.

"Whever you're ready."
Malachite stands at the other side of the room, tying his hair back.

He summons Star Platinum, just.. standing there. Patient.
*Let's get on with this,* he thinks to himself with a nod at Malachite.
He finishes tying his hair back with a flourish, then lunges forward, Hierophant darting at his chest.
Instead of dodging the attack like usual, Polaris stands there, using Star to grab the tendril coming towards his chest and wrapping it around the stands fist, yanking it to the side roughly.
Kakyoin yelps and rolls to the side. Hierophant Green slithers out of Polaris' grasp and returns to Malachite's side, solidifying into a humanoid shape and leaking a shimmering fluid from its palms.
*Emerald Splash... It won't work,* he thought, stopping time for only a few seconds, running up to Hierophant and aiming its hands back at Malachite before jumping back, time resuming.

*"Shit-"*
Malachite jumps aside, flinging a few razor-sharp droplets at Polaris.
Polaris blocks himself with Star Platinums arms, feeling the scrapes in his skin but ignoring them— they're small. They don't matter.

Taking a moment to settle down, he cracks his fists. *My turn.*
He syncs up his leg with Star's, using it to launch himself forward and aim his fist at Malachite.
The punch lands just before Malachite snatches himself to the side with his stand. He flinches and tries to spear Polaris with a cluster of tentacles.

All of the sudden, Star used star finger, twisting its hand so that it roughly hit the side of Malachite's neck as he ducked underneath the tentacles. He shoved Malachite to the ground using Star, before tackling Malachite himself.

Malachite's dazed-- shit, he's pinned, how--?
He knows he can't throw Polaris off with strength alone while he's straddling him like this, so he calls upon his stand, trying to force it down Polaris' throat.

He smiles, adrenaline pumping harder— *Finally, things are getting somewhere.*
Polaris rolls over so that Malachite is on top of him, syncing up both of Star's legs with his own and kicking Malachite's stomach, knocking the smaller off of him.
His mind races as he tries to regain his breath and his balance. Hierophant worms its way into any entrance it can find; crawling into Polaris' mouth, his nose, his tear ducts-

Stopping time, Polaris grabs multiple tentacles in each hand and rips them out, yanking Malachite and tying them around him.
*Time resumes.*
Thin tears appear in his skin. He hisses, unraveling the strands and pouncing at Polaris.
Polaris grabs Malachite's wrists before they can reach him, holding him in place and headbutting him.

There's a sickening crack. The room spins. Malachite's head lolls weakly to the side, blood trickling from his nose and running down his chin.
"Hahh, *fuck... you."*
